'''Ray Kendry Páez Andrade''' (born 4 May 2007) is an Ecuadorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] or [[right winger]] for [[Argentine Primera División]] club [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]], on loan from {{English football updater|Chelsea}} club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Guayaquil]], Páez began his career with local side [[Barcelona S.C.|Barcelona]]'s youth department Academia Alfaro Moreno at the age of five. [[Barcelona S.C.|Barcelona SC]] was offered the chance to register Páez at the age of eight, but the club did not sign him as it was "too hard for a president to pay for a player at this age".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elvar.com.ec/noticias/2023/04/25/1251-revelan-el-motivo-por-el-cual-barcelona-sc-no-ficho-a-kendry-paez|title=Revelan el motivo por el cual Barcelona SC no fichó a Kendry Páez|trans-title=Revealed the reason why Barcelona SC did not sign Kendry Páez|publisher=El VAR|language=es|date=25 April 2023|accessdate=5 June 2023|archive-date=5 June 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230605203223/https://www.elvar.com.ec/noticias/2023/04/25/1251-revelan-el-motivo-por-el-cual-barcelona-sc-no-ficho-a-kendry-paez|url-status=dead}}</ref> He later had a short stint at [[C.S. Emelec|Emelec]] before moving to [[C.S. Patria|Patria]], where he started to feature more regularly as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elcomercio.com/deportes/futbol/kendry-paez-barcelona-emelec-independiente-valle.html|title=Kendry Páez pasó por Barcelona y Emelec antes de llegar a Independiente del Valle|trans-title=Kendry Páez represented Barcelona and Emelec before arriving at Independiente del Valle|publisher=[[El Comercio (Ecuador)|El Comercio]]|language=es|date=2 March 2023|accessdate=5 June 2023|archive-date=5 June 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230605203223/https://www.elcomercio.com/deportes/futbol/kendry-paez-barcelona-emelec-independiente-valle.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Independiente del Valle===
Páez joined [[Independiente del Valle]] in 2018, aged 12. His performances for their youth team, including being named most outstanding player at the 2022 Next Generation Trophy in [[Salzburg]], [[Austria]], drew the attention of multiple clubs across Europe.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.benditofutbol.com/legionarios/kendry-paez-promesa-fichaje-europa.html|title=Kendry Paéz, promesa tricolor, es buscado desde Europa|trans-title=Kendry Paéz, tricolor promise, is wanted from Europe|first=Paulo|last=Álvarez|date=16 January 2023|accessdate=29 January 2023|website=benditofutbol.com|language=Spanish|archive-date=29 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230129005252/https://www.benditofutbol.com/legionarios/kendry-paez-promesa-fichaje-europa.html|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/futbol/kendry-paez-la-joya-guayaquilena-de-15-anos-que-brilla-en-las-formativas-de-independiente-del-valle-y-que-interesa-a-los-mejores-clubes-de-europa-nota/|title=Kendry Páez, la joya guayaquileña de 15 años que brilla en las formativas de Independiente del Valle y que interesa a clubes importantes de Europa|trans-title=Kendry Páez, the 15-year-old jewel from Guayaquil who shines in the training sessions of Independiente del Valle and who interests important clubs in Europe|date=18 January 2023|accessdate=29 January 2023|website=eluniverso.com|language=Spanish|archive-date=29 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230129005255/https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/futbol/kendry-paez-la-joya-guayaquilena-de-15-anos-que-brilla-en-las-formativas-de-independiente-del-valle-y-que-interesa-a-los-mejores-clubes-de-europa-nota/|url-status=live}}</ref> He reportedly attracted interest from German club [[Borussia Dortmund]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ole.com.ar/ecuador/independiente-del-valle/borussia-dortmund-busca-fichar-kendry-paez-juvenil-promesa-15-anos_0_PQ0GLfUVjc.html|title=Exclusivo: el club europeo que ya habló con IDV para fichar a Kendry Páez|trans-title=Exclusive: the European club that already spoke with IDV to sign Kendry Páez|date=16 January 2023|accessdate=29 January 2023|website=ole.com.ar|language=Spanish}}</ref> while English side [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] had an opening bid for Páez rejected in December 2022.<ref name=ole>{{cite web|url=https://www.ole.com.ar/ecuador/independiente-del-valle/kendry-paez-juvenil-promocion-primer-equipo-rayados_0_9IGOiqKVjx.html|title=La importante decisión que tomó IDV con Kendry Páez|trans-title=The important decision that IDV made with Kendry Páez|date=15 December 2022|accessdate=29 January 2023|website=ole.com.ar|language=Spanish|archive-date=29 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230129005244/https://www.ole.com.ar/ecuador/independiente-del-valle/kendry-paez-juvenil-promocion-primer-equipo-rayados_0_9IGOiqKVjx.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

He was promoted to the Independiente del Valle's first team for the 2023 pre-season, at the age of fifteen.<ref name=ole/> On 25 February 2023, he marked his highly anticipated professional debut with a goal; the third in a 3–1 [[Ecuadorian Serie A]] win over [[Mushuc Runa S.C.|Mushuc Runa]]. Having received a lifted cut-back on the right-hand side of the penalty area from [[Anthony Landázuri]], he instinctively floated the ball over the goalkeeper, [[Jorge Pinos]], on the volley into the far corner of the goal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ole.com.ar/ecuador/independiente-del-valle/kendry-paez-debut-independiente-del-valle-mushuc-runa_0_wJG4XhCssc.html|title=Así fue el debut de Kendry Páez: mucha voluntad, valentía y golazo|trans-title=This was the debut of Kendry Páez: a lot of will, courage and a great goal|date=25 February 2023|accessdate=26 February 2023|website=ole.com.ar|language=Spanish|archive-date=26 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226001022/https://www.ole.com.ar/ecuador/independiente-del-valle/kendry-paez-debut-independiente-del-valle-mushuc-runa_0_wJG4XhCssc.html|url-status=live}}</ref> In doing so, he became the youngest debutant, and youngest goal-scorer, in the Ecuadorian top flight.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.relevo.com/futbol/liga-ecuador/kendry-paez-nueva-perla-sudamerica-20230225223821-nt.html|title=Kendry Páez, la nueva perla de Sudamérica: 15 años, debut con gol y rumbo a Europa|trans-title=Kendry Páez, the new pearl of South America: 15 years old, debut with a goal and heading to Europe|first=Patxo|last=De la Rica|date=25 February 2023|accessdate=26 February 2023|website=relevo.com|language=Spanish|archive-date=26 February 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230226000340/https://www.relevo.com/futbol/liga-ecuador/kendry-paez-nueva-perla-sudamerica-20230225223821-nt.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Chelsea===
On 5 June 2023, it was announced that Páez would join [[Premier League]] club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] after his 18th birthday, in the summer of 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Paez to join Chelsea |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/paez-to-join-chelsea |access-date=5 June 2023 |website=www.chelseafc.com |language=en-gb |archive-date=5 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230605143829/https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/paez-to-join-chelsea |url-status=live }}</ref>

====Strasbourg (loan)====
On 31 July 2025, Páez joined [[Ligue 1]] club [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]] on a season-long loan.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kendry Paez joins Strasbourg on loan |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/kendry-paez-joins-strasbourg-on-loan |access-date=31 July 2025 |website=www.chelseafc.com |language=en-gb }}</ref>

====RIver Plate (loan)====
On 31 January 2026, Páez joined [[Club Atlético River Plate|River Plate]] on a one-year loan.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kendry Paez makes loan switch to River Plate |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/article/kendry-paez-makes-loan-switch-to-river-plate |access-date=31 January 2026 |website=www.chelseafc.com |language=en-gb }}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Paéz has represented Ecuador at under-17 level, scoring against both [[Argentina national under-17 football team|Argentina]] and [[Colombia national under-17 football team|Colombia]].<ref name=ole/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ole.com.ar/ecuador/la-tri/kendry-paez-mini-tri-gol-maradona-argentina-clubes-europa_0_JkTTqya9xT.html|title=Video de Kendry Páez, la nueva joya de Ecuador: un golazo a Argentina 'a lo Maradona' y mirado por los grandes de Europa|trans-title=Video of Kendry Páez, the new jewel of Ecuador: a great goal against Argentina 'a la Maradona' and watched by the greats of Europe|date=27 October 2022|accessdate=29 January 2023|website=ole.com.ar|language=Spanish|archive-date=29 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230129005245/https://www.ole.com.ar/ecuador/la-tri/kendry-paez-mini-tri-gol-maradona-argentina-clubes-europa_0_JkTTqya9xT.html|url-status=live}}</ref> He was left out of Ecuador's under-20 squad for the [[2023 South American U-20 Championship]] to facilitate his transition into the Independiente del Valle first team squad.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/futbol/estos-son-los-ecuatorianos-que-estan-en-el-extranjero-y-no-fueron-convocados-para-el-sudamericano-sub-20-colombia-2023-nota/|title=Estos son los ecuatorianos que están en el extranjero y no fueron convocados para el Sudamericano Sub-20 Colombia 2023|trans-title=These are the Ecuadorians who are abroad and were not called up for the South American Sub-20 Colombia 2023|date=9 January 2023|accessdate=29 January 2023|website=eluniverso.com|language=Spanish|archive-date=23 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230123183547/https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/futbol/estos-son-los-ecuatorianos-que-estan-en-el-extranjero-y-no-fueron-convocados-para-el-sudamericano-sub-20-colombia-2023-nota/|url-status=live}}</ref>

He was called up to the Ecuador under-17 squad again for the [[2023 South American U-17 Championship]] in March 2023. In their first game, he provided an assist for Ecuador's second goal in their 2–2 comeback draw with [[Brazil national under-17 football team|Brazil]] - a through-ball from his own half which was then converted by teammate Geremy de Jesús.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.futbolecuador.com/site/noticia/kendry-paez-lidero-a-la-tri-sub-17-en-un-debut-que-ilusiona/154118|title=¡Kendry Páez lideró a La Tri Sub 17 en un debut que ilusiona!|trans-title=Kendry Páez led La Tri Sub 17 in an exciting debut!|date=31 March 2023|accessdate=31 March 2023|website=futbolecuador.com|language=Spanish|archive-date=31 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230331120532/https://www.futbolecuador.com/site/noticia/kendry-paez-lidero-a-la-tri-sub-17-en-un-debut-que-ilusiona/154118|url-status=live}}</ref> Páez was included in Ecuador's squad for the [[2023 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in Argentina; he was the youngest player to be included in the final squad of any of the participating nations in the tournament. On 26 May, Páez scored a goal in Ecuador's 9–0 win over [[Fiji national under-20 football team|Fiji]], becoming the youngest player to score in the FIFA U20 World Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/for-ecuadorian-history-maker-kendry-paez-age-is-no-barrier|title=For Ecuadorian history-maker Kendry Paez age is no barrier|date=1 June 2023|accessdate=13 September 2023|publisher=FIFA|archive-date=30 June 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230630154509/https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/for-ecuadorian-history-maker-kendry-paez-age-is-no-barrier|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Senior===
On 5 June 2023, Páez was called up to the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador senior squad]] for the first time.<ref>{{Cite tweet|user=LaTri|number=1665814822691172353|title=Nuestros 𝗰𝗼𝗻𝘃𝗼𝗰𝗮𝗱𝗼𝘀 🔥 🫡 Ellos son los elegidos por el DT Félix Sánchez Bas para la doble fecha FIFA de Junio 💪 Tío @PilsenerEcuador a celebrar que regresa #LaTri #PiensaEnGrande🇪🇨|trans-title=Our summoned players 🔥 🫡 They are the ones chosen by DT Félix Sánchez Bas for the double FIFA date of June 💪 Uncle @PilsenerEcuador to celebrate the return of #LaTri #PiensaEnGrande🇪🇨}}</ref>

On 12 September 2023, Páez made his debut with the senior team, starting in a 2–1 [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|World Cup qualifier]] win over [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] and providing the assist for [[Félix Torres (footballer, born 1997)|Félix Torres]]' match winning goal. Thus, he became the youngest player ever to represent ''La Tri'' and the second youngest South American to ever play international football behind [[Diego Maradona]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Cons|first=Roddy|url=https://en.as.com/soccer/ecuador-and-future-chelsea-star-kendry-paez-second-only-to-diego-maradona-in-south-america-n/|title=Ecuador and future Chelsea star Kendry Páez second only to Diego Maradona in South America|date=13 September 2023|accessdate=13 September 2023|publisher=AS|archive-date=2 December 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231202215548/https://en.as.com/soccer/ecuador-and-future-chelsea-star-kendry-paez-second-only-to-diego-maradona-in-south-america-n/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 12 October, he scored his first goal for Ecuador in a 2–1 win over [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]], becoming the youngest ever goalscorer in [[CONMEBOL]] World Cup qualifiers at the age of 16 years and 161 days.<ref>{{cite news |date=2023-10-13 |title=Paez breaks record with Ecuador goal |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/articles/c974x3gxnywo.amp |accessdate=2024-04-27 |publisher=BBC |language=en |archive-date=2023-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231022211418/https://www.bbc.com/sport/articles/c974x3gxnywo.amp |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |date=2023-10-13 |title=Why Chelsea wonderkid is still breaking records in Ecuador |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67104574 |access-date=2024-04-27 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB |archive-date=2024-06-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240624211812/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67104574 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 29 May 2024, he was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/futbol/ecuador-presenta-lista-oficial-para-la-copa-america-gonzalo-plata-y-robert-arboleda-quedaron-relegados-nota/|title=Ecuador presenta lista oficial para la Copa América: Gonzalo Plata y Robert Arboleda quedaron relegados|trans-title=Ecuador presents official roster for Copa America: Gonzalo Plata and Robert Arboleda left off the list|publisher=[[El Universo]]|date=29 May 2024|language=es|access-date=27 June 2024|archive-date=4 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240604184809/https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/futbol/ecuador-presenta-lista-oficial-para-la-copa-america-gonzalo-plata-y-robert-arboleda-quedaron-relegados-nota/|url-status=live}}</ref> On 26 June, he scored a penalty in a 3–1 victory against [[Jamaica national football team|Jamaica]], becoming the second youngest scorer in the competition, aged 17 years and 53 days, following [[Johnnier Montaño]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Booker |first=Adam |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/kendry-paez-makes-copa-am-231100049.html |title=👶 Kendry Páez makes Copa América history with penalty strike |publisher=Yahoo Sports |date=27 June 2024 }}</ref>

==Style of play==
Paéz took inspiration from fellow Ecuadorian [[Gonzalo Plata]] and Argentine [[Lionel Messi]], both of whom he watched as a child, to improve his own dribbling ability.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lacancha.com.ec/2022/10/27/kendry-paez-es-la-nueva-joya-de-independiente-del-valle/|title=Kendry Páez es la nueva joya de Independiente del Valle|trans-title=Kendry Páez is the new jewel of Independiente del Valle|date=27 October 2022|accessdate=29 January 2023|website=lacancha.com.ec|language=Spanish|archive-date=29 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230129005244/https://lacancha.com.ec/2022/10/27/kendry-paez-es-la-nueva-joya-de-independiente-del-valle/|url-status=live}}</ref>

